[30;1m62 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m63 | [0m[35m    Only `seconds` can be a float. All other arguments are integers.[0m
[30;1m64 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35m    Note that `days=1` will trigger the function the same time every day.[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35m    This does not have the same behavior as `seconds=84000` since days have[0m
[30;1m67 | [0m[35m    different lengths due to daylight savings and leap seconds. Similarly,[0m
[30;1m68 | [0m[35m    using `months=1` will trigger the function on the same day each month.[0m
